      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IRINKA WAYNE (3) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten one length, (22.63) at this track. Speedy beginner who should be prominent early on from an inside box. Can go on with it. POKER NISMO (2) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 3.5 lengths back in second (22.60) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Hard to beat again. NOT CLIFFORD (1) was always prominent from this same draw last time and boxed on well to place (22.82) in a Grade 5 over 400m at this track. Expecting another bold showing. TORNADO ETHICS (6) is a last start winner who can measure up again.",
